   "abstract": "Ruha Benjamin defines the New Jim Code as the employment of new technologies that reflect and reproduce existing inequities while being promoted and perceived as more objective or progressive than the discriminatory systems of an earlier era. She develops it across four dimensions, engineered inequity, default discrimination, coded exposure, and technological benevolence, to show that a system can carry racism forward by design without any individual intending it. The book is the spine of the course, and its subtitle, abolitionist tools, frames her closing argument: refuse the unjust system rather than reform it.",
